sftp://username@server.example.com:22/home/username


or.... the better way
sudo apt-get install sshfs
sudo mkdir /media/user/userFolder
sudo sshfs -o allow_other root@xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:/ /media/user/userFolder
        or via RSA key
sudo sshfs -o rw -o allow_other,IdentityFile=/home/XXX/.ssh/XXXX user@XX.XX.XX.XXX:/home/user /media/user/userFolder
